Package gw.api.webservice.maintenanceTools

Class ProcessStatus

java.lang.Object
gw.api.webservice.maintenanceTools.ProcessStatus
All Implemented Interfaces:
ProcessIDStatus, GWRemotable, Serializable
public final class ProcessStatus extends Object implements GWRemotable, Serializable, ProcessIDStatus
Contains information about the status of a previously started batch process. This could contain status information for a process that is currently running or for a process that ran was run in the past. If the process is not currently running, the opsCompleted and failedOps fields won't have any useful information.

    • ProcessStatus

      public ProcessStatus(String type, String serverId, Date created, Date startDate, Date dateCompleted, Integer opsCompleted, Integer failedOps, String failureReason, String returnValue)
      Note: The process is running if dateCompleted is null
      Parameters:
      type - the type of process
      serverId - the server that ran (or running) this batch process
      created - the date that the process was requested to start
      startDate - the date that the process started running
      dateCompleted - the date the process finished, if it has in fact finished
      opsCompleted - the number of operations the process completed
      failedOps - the number of failed operations
      failureReason - if the process failed to complete, the reason why it failed
      returnValue - a short string value set by the called batch process as a return value
